go_data.justification: Tenascin contains fibronectin type III repeats, which are known to be involved in extracellular matrix organization.
The predicted protein of tenascin consists of a carboxy-terminal fibrinogen-like domain.
Tenascin contains EGF-like repeats, which are known to be involved in cell adhesion molecule binding.
Tenascin is predicted to be a large protein with multiple domains, suggesting it is located in the extracellular matrix.
